						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, central shrine, Tiruvālanduṟaiyār temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 9: 980 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 20 sheep to provide curd offerings thrice a day to God Tiruvālanduṟai Mahādēvar by Kaviśiyaṉ Nakkaṉ Māṟapirāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Nambi Ārūraṉ, who was the <hi rend="italic">kaṉmi</hi> (agent) of the Paḻuvēṭṭaraiyar chief Maṟavan Kaṇḍaṉār, who raised the temple in stone on the direction of the above chief at Śiṟupaḻuvūr.</p>						

						</summary>
